<p>From Wikipedia:</p>

<blockquote>
  <p>Visual literacy is the ability to <a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Interpreting" title="Interpreting">interpret</a>, negotiate, and make meaning from information presented in the form of an <a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Image" title="Image">image</a>, extending the meaning of <a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Literacy" title="Literacy">literacy</a>, which commonly signifies interpretation of a written or printed <a href="https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Written_language" title="Written language">text</a>.</p>
</blockquote>

